Q3 how do you choose theta?\
\
Theta is noise of the dynamics in the latent state. A large noise will allow larger jumps. A small noise will give a more static latent state. A large theta also allows your model to be more flexible on the data, that means that if you assumption is not true the model might still be able to describe the data.}